http://pms.heroku.com
Update database.yml
rake db:create
rake db:migrate
rake db:seed
To create Task Using email
If you are registered with application
You can send mail to "ca3d9d72c14b200a3afb@cloudmailin.net"
With Subject : - Create Task
you can pass different parameter as follows in mail body
[milestone] = Name #Milestone name In which You have to add task
[due_date]  = Date  #mm-dd-yyyy
[description] = Description of task
[name] = Name Of task
Above parameter are optional
I have tested with gmail with disabling rich text editor,
You have to first login with application with your email id
If Mail is received from this email id then it adds task







